Global Military Body-Worn Cameras Market Insights
Military Body-Worn Cameras Market size was valued at USD 1.25 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.85 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 12.15% from 2024 to 2030.

Military Body-Worn Cameras Market Overview
The global Military Body-Worn Cameras market size is valued at USD 453.4 million in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 880.1 million by 2032, growing at a CAGR of 8.9% from 2025 to 2032. This growth is attributed to the increasing adoption of advanced surveillance technologies by military forces worldwide to enhance operational efficiency and ensure security. The demand for these devices is driven by their ability to capture real-time video footage during military operations, which enhances transparency and accountability. With rising investments in defense technology, the market is expected to expand significantly in the coming years.

